# =============================================================================
# .gitignore — Let's Encrypt Phase-2 hermetic stack (§11.4.10 / §11.4.30)
# =============================================================================
# NEVER version: the real .env (may hold non-secret local values but is the
# per-host copy), ACME account keys, issued certs + private keys, Caddy /data,
# and any materialized secret/CA file. The token itself is a Podman secret and
# never lands on disk here at all. Regeneration mechanism (§11.4.77): certs +
# account key are re-issued via ACME on loss; pebble.minica.pem is the public
# test CA copied from the pebble image.
# =============================================================================

# Local per-host env (the tracked template is .env.example)
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# ACME account keys, certs, private keys, CSRs (any runtime crypto material)
*.key
*.pem
*.crt
*.csr
*.p12
*.pfx

# Caddy persistent data / config (mirrors the named volumes; if ever bind-mounted)
data/
config/
caddy-data/
caddy-config/

# Materialized Pebble public test CA (regenerable from the pebble image)
pebble-ca/

# Any stray secret file (defense-in-depth; secrets are Podman secrets, not files)
secrets/
*.secret
*_token

# Generated per-boot by phase3_hermetic_issue.sh (live challtestsrv IP) — §11.4.77 regen mechanism
coredns/Corefile
